<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="jn1034r"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="jn1" href="#jn1034">JN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/jn1all.htm#jn1034r"> (NLI.2A) 34(r)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> &ldquo;Synge&apos;s play is Greek, said Yeats, &amp;c.&rdquo; </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Yeats gave Joyce this opinion of <cite>Riders to the Sea</cite> when he was engaged in trying to find work for both young men in London, while Joyce was on his way to Paris in 1903. Joyce resented this praise, and when he saw Synge and his manuscript in Paris attacked the play as un-Aristotelian, concealing that grudging admiration which led him to translate it into Italian some years later.</mm> </dd></dl>
